<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Venezuela-Floods,0126</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Three dead in Venezuelan Floods</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Flood waters swept away two people in
a car and killed a third person struggling to save them during
seasonal rains that have forced the evacuations of 2,000 people,
news reports said.
   The two people in the car, a man and his 7-year-old son, were
traveling Thursday in the eastern state of Zulia about 400 miles
east of Caracas, local newspapers said Friday. They were washed
away by a creek that overflowed, the reports said.
   A man passing by tried to rescue them but was also swept away by
the water, the reports said.
   Seasonal flooding in the east has also left about 3,000 acres of
farmland under water.
</TEXT>
