<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Berlin-Escape     09-03 0107</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Berlin-Escape,0110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two East Germans Swim to West</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two East Germans made a pre-dawn escape to the
West by swimming 500 yards across a river with their shoes on, West
Berlin police said.
   An East German patrol boat spotted the pair swimming across the
Havel River on Friday, but no shots were fired, said a police
official speaking on condition of anonymity.
   The Havel River flows through West Berlin into communist East
Germany.
   Police said the two drenched men hopped aboard a bus after their
swim and later reported to West Berlin officials. The bus driver
let them ride for free, police said.
</TEXT>
