<HEAD>Death Toll In Bus Accident Rises To 32</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The death toll from a bus accident
west of Sarajevo increased to 32 after rescue workers pulled the
body of a woman from a lake, the Tanjug news agency said.
   The state-run news agency said 10 children were among the dead.
   The bus plunged 50 yards into the water Wednesday when the
driver swerved to avoid a pile of bricks that had tmbled into the
road from the back of a truck.
   The bus was carrying mostly factory workers and their families
home to Paracin, 170 miles east of Sarajevo, from an Adriatic
vacation.
</TEXT>
