<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Reagan     09-03 0144</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Reagan,130</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Reagan To Make Stops in Nebraska, Louisville, Ky., on Return Trip</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan planned to spend a
quiet Labor Day weekend in his home state before making appearances
at a Nebraska college and addressing an American Legion convention
en route back to Washington on Tuesday.
   Presidential spokesman B. Jay Cooper said Friday the president
and his wife, Nancy, would spend the final weekend of their 21-day
California vacation at their 688-acre ranch north of Santa Barbara.
   On Tuesday, Reagan was scheduled to visit Hastings College in
Nebraska and then later address the annual convention of the
American Legion in Louisville, Ky., before arriving in Washington
on Tuesday night.
   At the Hastings campus Reagan was to dedicate the Gray Center
for the Communications Arts. The center is named for Robert T.
Gray, a Washington public relations executive.
</TEXT>
