<FILEID>AP-NR-09-03-88 0351EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a PM-HolyShoes     09-03 0251</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Holy Shoes,0259</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Evangelist Oral Roberts Reaching Out For Followers' Soles</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TULSA, Okla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Television evangelist Oral Roberts is asking
his followers to follow in his footsteps in a plan to stamp the
name of Jesus on their soles _ of their footwear, that is.
   In a recent letter to contributors and ``prayer partners,''
Roberts encouraged them to write ``Jesus'' on the heels of their
shoes.
   ``As you put your foot down, know by your faith you're bruising
the devil's head,'' the evangelist wrote in the letter. ``The devil
should always see the sole of your shoe coming down on him.''
   ``I really get a kick out of doing this,'' Roberts says in the
letter.
   The recommendation is made to followers in a four-page mailing
in which Roberts also asks for contributions to maintain his
medical missions programs.
   Roberts provides a rectangle on one page for supporters to
outline the soles of their shoes with a pen.
   ``Then, right where the heel of your shoe is outlined, write the
word `Jesus,''' Roberts said in the letter.
   The shoe outline is ``a point of contact to release your faith
for your miracle,'' he said. ``I've done it and I want you to do
it.''
   But the name of Jesus shouldn't be limited to the paper outline,
Roberts said.
   ``Next, write `Jesus' on the bottom of your actual shoe heel.
You ought to see the bottom of my shoes _ `Jesus' is written on
them,'' he said. ``I'm serious about it.''
</TEXT>
