<1ST_LINE>r a PM-IceCreamKilling     09-03 0200</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Ice Cream Killing,0204</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mother Shot To Death Inside Ice Cream Truck As Children Watch</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A mother of five working in a Mister Softee ice
cream truck was shot to death by two men posing as customers as her
husband and two children watched, police said.
   Rosa Vera, 35, was at the sales window of the truck when gunmen
approached and signaled they wanted to buy ice cream Thursday
night, police said.
   When she opened the window, one of the gunmen fired, hitting her
in the head, police said Friday. She died five minutes later at St.
John's Episcopal Hospital, in the borough of Queens.
   ``She did not try to resist,'' said Detective Sgt. James
Harkins. ``Apparently the gunman fired right away.''
   Mrs. Vera's husband, Enrique, 34, who was driving the truck,
said he did not believe words were exchanged, but could not be sure
because of the noise from the truck's bells and music, Harkins said.
   Two of the couple's five sons, Pablo, 5, and Chris, 3, were at
their mother's side when she was shot, police said.
   There was no apparent motive for the killing, police said,
adding that no money was taken.
</TEXT>
