<DOCNO> AP880903-0106 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-09-03-88 1501EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Obit-Melen     09-03 0126</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Obit-Melen,0130</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Former Turkish Prime Minister Dead at 82</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANKARA, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Prime Minister Ferit Melen died
Saturday of heart trouble, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency
reported. He was 82.
   Melen served as finance minister in several governments and was
named prime minister in 1972 during a succession of ``above party''
governments after a military takeover resulted in several
appointments to the Turkish cabinet.
   In the October 1973 general elections, Bulent Ecevit was elected
prime minister to replace Melen as part of a coalition government.
Turgut Ozal is the current prime minister.
   Melen also served as defense minister in the late 1970s. In 1986
he cofounded a minor political party that stressed closer Turkish
ties to the United States and the Western world.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
