living in Fort Lauderdale, according to the spokesman.
   Haley later told an unidentified minister and an unidentified
Supreme Court employee of ``similar intentions,'' said Dempsey.
   Haley was arrested by the U.S. Supreme Court police and agents
of the U.S. Marshal's Service and the FBI.
