<1ST_LINE>r a AM-StabbingDeaths     09-03 0323</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Stabbing Deaths,0333</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mother Charged In Children's Killings</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DOUG FISHER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A mother who went screaming to neighbors
that someone was stabbing her two children was later charged with
murdering them, police said Saturday.
   Angelinta Urena, 32, was charged in the deaths of Kelly America
Pena, 4, and her brother, Pershi ``Pepsi'' Pena, 8, detective Capt.
Bernard Gannon said.
   He said she would be arraigned Sunday if a judge was available.
   Ms. Urena, who was led from the slaying scene in handcuffs,
originally told police that a man had killed her children, Gannon
said.
   ``She became a stronger suspect in various phases of the
investigation as it went along, and that led to the charges,'' he
said.
   Gannon declined to specify what led police to suspect Ms. Urena
and he declined to speculate on a motive.
   Neighbors told television station WLNE they learned of the
slayings about 7 a.m. when Ms. Urena ran across the street naked
and screaming for help, saying someone was attacking her children.
   ``She came here and she wanted to use the phone, but they were
asking her, why, why, and she wouldn't answer. She would just say
that she needed to call police, that they were killing her
children,'' neighbor Maria Gomez told television station WJAR.
   The girl was found on her bed and the boy was on the floor of
the upstairs bedroom of their apartment, Gannon said.
   ``We don't know if they were stabbed in their beds or carried
there or what,'' he said. Only Ms. Urena and the children lived in
the home, Gannon said.
   Kelly was dead at the scene, but rescue crews detected a slight
pulse and rushed Pershi to Rhode Island Hospital, where he died,
Gannon said.
   Gannon said the children suffered multiple stab wounds. A fire
department dispatcher said rescue crews reported the boy may have
been stabbed as many as 15 times.
</TEXT>
