<HEAD>UNDATED: ... boost consumption.''</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Here are some commodity price trends during the past week:
   Grain and soybean futures advanced on the Chicago Board of Trade.
   Wheat for September delivery settled Friday at $4.01 a bushel
compared with $3.90 a week earlier; September corn rose to $2.90{ a
bushel from $2.77\; September oats climbed to $2.59{ a bushel from
$2.54; and September soybeans rallied to $8.73 a bushel from $8.31.
